1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,840
It is moving day.

2
00:00:02,840 --> 00:00:07,840
I have spent the last month here at Dwight's lovely farm

3
00:00:07,840 --> 00:00:10,240
taking a little bit of a vacation, clearing my head

4
00:00:10,240 --> 00:00:14,000
after Jan and I, um...

5
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:17,080
No, I did not kill her.

6
00:00:17,080 --> 00:00:19,180
We were just at different places in our lives,

7
00:00:19,180 --> 00:00:21,180
so I thought I'd be the bigger man

8
00:00:21,180 --> 00:00:23,180
and allow her to stay at the condo.

9
00:00:23,180 --> 00:00:24,480
She has since moved on.

10
00:00:24,480 --> 00:00:27,180
She is staying with her sister in Scottsdale.

11
00:00:27,180 --> 00:00:29,560
Fresh outlook, and it's all good.

12
00:00:29,580 --> 00:00:32,220
Okay, so look that over. Make sure it's accurate.

13
00:00:32,220 --> 00:00:33,220
What is this?

14
00:00:33,220 --> 00:00:37,520
Your bill, minus the 10% Dunder Meflin corporate discount.

15
00:00:37,520 --> 00:00:40,300
You're charging me? I'm your friend.

16
00:00:40,300 --> 00:00:42,660
You occupied the America Room for six weeks.

17
00:00:42,660 --> 00:00:43,900
That's our most popular room.

18
00:00:43,900 --> 00:00:46,700
There was no other guest the entire time I was here.

19
00:00:46,700 --> 00:00:49,440
Right, because you were in the America Room

20
00:00:49,440 --> 00:00:51,440
in an election year.

21
00:00:51,440 --> 00:00:53,140
Okay.

22
00:00:53,140 --> 00:00:56,240
All right, Dwight, take my money. Go ahead.

23
00:00:56,240 --> 00:00:57,580
Keep in mind that this whole thing

24
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:59,240
was just a business transaction.

25
00:00:59,240 --> 00:01:04,240
The late nights, the talks, slumber parties,

26
00:01:04,240 --> 00:01:07,140
the crying jags, that was all business.

27
00:01:07,140 --> 00:01:10,320
It had nothing to do with friendship

28
00:01:10,320 --> 00:01:12,820
and being friends.

29
00:01:12,820 --> 00:01:15,820
You can ring me up.

30
00:01:15,820 --> 00:01:17,820
Go ahead.

31
00:01:17,820 --> 00:01:20,820
Thank you, Dwight.

32
00:01:20,820 --> 00:01:22,820
We don't take debit cards anyway.

33
00:01:22,820 --> 00:01:25,820
Dwight, a little help with the bags, please?

34
00:01:47,820 --> 00:01:50,820
WB Jones is renovating their offices,

35
00:01:50,820 --> 00:01:52,820
and their construction crews are taking up

36
00:01:52,820 --> 00:01:54,820
some of the parking spaces we used to get.

37
00:01:54,820 --> 00:01:57,820
So we had to park at a satellite parking lot over there.

38
00:01:57,820 --> 00:02:00,820
Which just means we get to see more of our lovely street.

39
00:02:00,820 --> 00:02:02,820
Tell them what we saw today, Jim.

40
00:02:02,820 --> 00:02:05,820
Oh, today we saw a junkyard dog attacking the bones

41
00:02:05,820 --> 00:02:07,820
of a rotisserie dog.

42
00:02:07,820 --> 00:02:09,820
That's a good one.

43
00:02:09,820 --> 00:02:11,820
I'm glad you're here.

44
00:02:11,820 --> 00:02:13,820
I'm glad you're here.

45
00:02:13,820 --> 00:02:15,820
I'm glad you're here.

46
00:02:15,820 --> 00:02:18,820
A junkyard dog attacking the bones of a rotisserie chicken.

47
00:02:18,820 --> 00:02:20,820
Nature.

48
00:02:20,820 --> 00:02:22,820
I've been here nine years now.

49
00:02:22,820 --> 00:02:24,820
All of a sudden I'm supposed to park half a mile away.

50
00:02:24,820 --> 00:02:27,820
I lost a penny out of my lopers, Oscar.

51
00:02:27,820 --> 00:02:29,820
I will quit.

52
00:02:29,820 --> 00:02:33,820
As God is my witness, I will quit if this is not fixed.

53
00:02:33,820 --> 00:02:36,820
Some of us like the walk more than others.

54
00:02:36,820 --> 00:02:38,820
It looks like hell.

55
00:02:45,820 --> 00:02:47,820
Hey, Stanley.

56
00:02:47,820 --> 00:02:49,820
Ugh.

57
00:02:55,820 --> 00:02:57,820
Did you pick a new chair? It's been a while.

58
00:02:57,820 --> 00:03:00,820
Pam, when I first opened this catalog,

59
00:03:00,820 --> 00:03:03,820
I thought I was just going to be picking out a chair.

60
00:03:03,820 --> 00:03:05,820
But instead you found something to distract you

61
00:03:05,820 --> 00:03:07,820
from ever picking out a chair.

62
00:03:07,820 --> 00:03:09,820
Michael started the process of selecting a new chair

63
00:03:09,820 --> 00:03:11,820
about three weeks ago.

64
00:03:11,820 --> 00:03:13,820
And normally I wouldn't care, but he promised me his old one.

65
00:03:13,820 --> 00:03:15,820
It's way better. It's one of these.

66
00:03:15,820 --> 00:03:17,820
Shh.

67
00:03:17,820 --> 00:03:19,820
I really want it.

68
00:03:20,820 --> 00:03:22,820
Have you ever seen this woman?

69
00:03:22,820 --> 00:03:24,820
Her? The one in the really great

70
00:03:24,820 --> 00:03:26,820
mesh black high-backed swivel chair?

71
00:03:26,820 --> 00:03:28,820
Look at her smile.
